HEADWORD: Father-lasher
<hw>Fa"ther-lash`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A European marine fish (<spn>Cottus bubalis</spn>), allied to the
sculpin; -- called also <altname>lucky proach</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

